description:
Error-detecting normal self-dual CSS code on three qubit pairs that encodes a logical qubit pair and detects any error acting on one pair \cite{arxiv:quant-ph/0410199}.
In Knill's \(C_4/C_6\) architecture, this code is used at the second and higher concatenation levels.

A stabilizer tableau for the code is given by \cite[ID 126]{preset:qiskit}
\begin{align}
\begin{array}{cccccc}
  Z & Z & Z & Z & I & I \\
  Z & Z & I & I & Z & Z \\
  X & X & X & X & I & I \\
  X & X & I & I & X & X
\end{array}~.
\end{align}
Its logical operators are \(X_L = IIXXII\), \(Z_L = ZIIZZI\), \(X_S = IXIXXI\), and \(Z_S = IIIIZZ\) \cite{arxiv:quant-ph/0410199}.

