  I & I & Z & I & Z & I & Z & Z \\
  Z & I & Z & I & I & Z & I & Z \\
  X & X & X & X & X & X & X & X
\end{array}~.
\end{align}

In encoded IQP sampling, the final measurement outcomes determine both the logical sample and stabilizer checks, enabling end-of-circuit error detection or postselected decoding directly from the classical samples \cite{arxiv:2404.19005}.

